Most galaxies we are familiar with fall into one of two easily-identified types: spiral galaxies or elliptical galaxies. 

But other galaxies require in-depth study to understand them. This is the case with the galaxy NGC 4694 featured in this NASA/ESA @HUBBLE_space picture.
